  "original_title": "\u0db1\u0dc0 \u0d9c\u0db8\u0db1\u0d9a\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0da7 \u0dad\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dda \u0dbb\u0dcf\u0da2\u0dca\u200d\u0dba \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0da0\u0dab\u0dca\u0da9\u0dad\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dba\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Instead of a new journey, there is state violence",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Mr. Sajith Premadasa, the leader of the opposition, said that the first attack on the people's democratic struggle was launched on the ninth day of May by launching state violence, and the result was that the Prime Minister had to go home.",
        "He said that it extended to the expulsion of the President from the country and through the proceedings that followed, all those who were hoping for a new journey had to experience state violence instead.",
        "The leader of the opposition said that the state violence is taking place seriously and instead of a new journey, there is the same old violent journey.",
        "He said that there is a situation where a president who became the ruler of the country with a majority of 69 lakhs has been expelled from the country by a public struggle.",
        "He said this when a special meeting of the National Reform Movement was held at the opposition leader's office in Colombo today (25). The purpose of this is to get positive ideas and suggestions for creating a more progressive country.",
        "A group of political party leaders, parliamentary public representatives and professionals were present. He said that an appointed dictatorship should not be allowed to act like a democracy in this country, but the rulers should set an example of unity and fairness."
      ],
